sCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10203","id":"10203","name":"Installation Guide"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"We are going to be using the stock dhcp package from 4.0.0 and onward, so we need to:\r\n\r\n* Add a section in the upgrade docs that explains how the user is supposed to switch to the stock package. There should be a note to the user that it is optional for them to do this.\r\n* Add something in the release notes that says that Eucalyptus now uses the stock dhcp server package available in CentOS/RHEL.\r\n\r\n# Before starting Eucalyptus services after upgrade packages, you will need to edit /etc/eucalyptus/eucalyptus.conf on each CC and NC.\r\n# Change the value of VNET_DHCPDAEMON from /usr/sbin/dhcpd41 to /usr/sbin/dhcpd\r\n# After you have started all eucalyptus services as per the upgrade docs you'll need to ensure that dhcp is functioning correctly. Make sure that instances are being assigned addresses from the dhcp server.\r\n\r\nFailure to make this change will not prevent the cloud from functioning properly.  However, we will no longer maintain or ship it, so it will not be available for newly-installed machines, whose VNET_DHCPDAEMON options will be set to /usr/sbin/dhcpd out of the box.","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":"DOC-1124","customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Docs should explain how to switch to the stock dhcp package","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mspaulding","name":"mspaulding","key":"mspaulding","accountId":"557058:fa0a9514-613e-4c4f-8872-2880096382a5","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassi